title: Adult HIV. Test 4. Antiretroviral drugs


Which is one of the main current goals of antiretroviral treatment?
+	To suppress the viral load
-	To cure HIV infection
-	To allow the patient to have a pain-free death
-	To prevent repeated infection with HIV

How many classes of antiretroviral drugs are usually used in South Africa?
-	Two
+	Four
-	Five
-	Ten

Which of the following drugs is a ‘nuc’?
+	AZT
-	Nevirapine
-	Efavirenz
-	Lopinavir/ritonavir

Antiretroviral drugs for treatment should always be used:
-	Alone
-	In pairs
+	In combinations of three or more
-	Together with an antibiotic

Standardised regimens of treatment:
-	Have many disadvantages
+	Are simpler to use
-	Are more expensive than individualised treatment
-	Have a high risk of side effects

Which drug is part of the first-line combination?
+	TDF
-	Lopinavir/ritonavir
-	ddI
-	Rifampicin

Which drug is part of the second-line combination?
+	3TC
-	TDF
-	Nevirapine
-	Efavirenz

Both first- and second-line combinations contain:
+	Two ‘nucs’
-	Two ‘non-nucs’
-	Two ‘PIs’
-	All of the above

Which antiretroviral drug should not be taken during the first trimester of pregnancy?
-	AZT
-	Nevirapine
-	Lopinavir/ritonavir
+	All commonly used drugs are safe

Most first line antiretroviral drugs are taken:
+	Once a day
-	Twice a day
-	Three times a day
-	On an empty stomach

Minor side effects such as nausea, loose stools and tiredness are common with:
+	Most antiretroviral drugs during the first weeks of treatment
-	‘Nucs’ after the first six weeks of treatment
-	3TC if it is taken with meals
-	Efavirenz if it is taken on an empty stomach

A generalised rash is common with:
-	3TC
-	Lopinavir/ritonavir
+	Nevirapine
-	d4T

A sign of a serious rash which needs urgent treatment is:
-	A generalised pink rash in a patient who feels well
+	A blistering skin rash which also affects the mucous membranes of the mouth
-	A rash on the face and chest which lasts longer than a week
-	A rash which only appears after the first month of treatment

Clinical hepatitis with abdominal pain, jaundice and nausea is a serious side effect of:
-	AZT
-	3TC
+	Nevirapine
-	ddI

Anaemia is a well-recognised side effect of:
-	Efavirenz
-	TDF
-	Lopinavir/ritonavir
+	AZT

ddI and d4T should not be used together as they both may cause:
-	Severe headaches
+	Peripheral neuropathy
-	Severe skin rashes
-	Anaemia

A burning pain in the feet is a symptom of:
-	Lactic acidosis
+	Peripheral neuropathy
-	Nevirapine sensitivity
-	Pancreatitis

Lipodystrophy is a recognised side effect of:
-	Co-trimoxazole
-	Nevirapine
+	AZT
-	Anti-TB treatment

Weight loss, nausea, abdominal pain and tiredness after months of successful antiretroviral treatment suggests:
+	Lactic acidosis
-	Lipodystrophy
-	An emotional problem
-	Antiretroviral treatment is no longer effective

Which antiretroviral drug can cause renal damage?
+	Tenofovir
-	AZT
-	3TC
-	Nevirapine
